Hi,

biocLite() can now be used to download and install Bioconductor
developmental packages again.

Reminder:

  - "Bioconductor devel" is now Bioconductor 1.9.

  - The build/check results for "Bioconductor devel" are here:
      http://bioconductor.org/checkResults/1.9/

  - biocLite() knows which is the "right" version of Bioconductor
    for you. This depends on the version of R that you are using:
      R 2.2.z -> BioC 1.7
      R 2.3.z -> BioC 1.8
      R 2.4.z -> BioC 1.9

  - Doing this from R 2.4.0:
      > source("http://bioconductor.org/biocLite.R")
      > biocLite("Biobase")
    will install last Biobase devel (1.11.3).

Cheers,

H.

